\begin{CRITIC}
*   **Data-Hypothesis Alignment**: The current proposal lacks a mechanism to quantify "imperfection." Without a parameterized error model (e.g., scaling factors, noise injection, or structural mismatch), the "break-point" is ill-defined.
*   **Feasibility & Noise**: Pendulum-v1 is a low-dimensional, deterministic environment. The signal-to-noise ratio is extremely high; the agent will likely "learn around" minor inaccuracies in $\Phi(s)$ via the residual $f_\theta(s)$ effortlessly, failing to reveal a meaningful break-point.
